  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is the **second edition** (1697) of Thomas Gataker's monumental Latin edition of Marcus Aurelius' *Meditations* (*Ta eis heauton*, \"To Himself\"), first published in 1652. Gataker's edition is considered **\"the principal authority\"** on the text of the *Meditations* according to A.S.L. Farquharson, the foremost 20th-century Marcus Aurelius scholar. The 1697 edition was expanded with annotations by **André Dacier** (the leading French classical scholar of the era) and a biography attributed to \"Cornelio Stanhope\" — almost certainly **George Stanhope** (1660–1728), Dean of Canterbury. It was published in London by **Edward Millington**, one of the most famous book auctioneers of the 17th century, and features a portrait engraving likely by **William Faithorne the Elder** (c. 1616–1691), England's foremost portrait engraver.",
      "classified_as": [
